# General Project Audit

Run this when asked: "audit this project" or "run general audit"

---

SECTION 1 — ARCHITECTURE
- Overall structure and separation of concerns
- Patterns used and misused
- What a senior engineer would change first

SECTION 2 — CODE QUALITY
- Duplicated logic
- Inconsistent naming or style
- Functions doing too much
- Missing error handling
- Missing input validation
- Dead code or unused imports

SECTION 3 — SECURITY
- Exposed secrets or credentials
- Unvalidated inputs
- Insecure dependencies
- Auth/authz gaps

SECTION 4 — PERFORMANCE
- Obvious bottlenecks
- N+1 queries or bad DB patterns
- Missing indexes
- Heavy synchronous operations

SECTION 5 — DEPENDENCIES
- Outdated or risky packages
- Unnecessary dependencies
- Version conflicts

SECTION 6 — DEVOPS READINESS
- Deployable as-is?
- Missing env config
- Hardcoded values that should be env vars

SECTION 7 — TECHNICAL DEBT
- Top 5 things that will hurt at scale
- Priority: Critical / High / Medium / Low

---

OUTPUT FORMAT

For each issue:
- Location (file + line if possible)
- Problem
- Why it matters
- Recommended fix

End with:
PRIORITY ACTION LIST — top 10 fixes ordered by impact
